Data Fields

rlUInt8_t enableMode
 This field decides if the Delay or Dummy option is enabled or disabled
Mode Definition
0 - No Delay or Dummy Data (Disabled)
1 - HSI Data will have an additional configurable delay after ADC VALID and Configurable Dummy data after chirp data
2 - Similar to configuration 0x1 but the device varies the delay in each chirp
Others - Reserved
.
 
rlUInt8_t reserved0
 Reserved for future use.
 
rlUInt16_t reserved1
 Reserved for future use.
 
rlUInt16_t delayVal
 Delay Count value.
Mode DELAY_VAL Definition
0 NA
1 1 LSB = 20 ns delay
Delay Added = (DELAY_VAL*20ns) + 1.2us
2 Delay Added = Vary from chirp to chirp within MIN_DELAY to MAX_DELAY
MIN_DELAY = 1.1us
MAX_DELAY = 1.2us + (DELAY_VAL * 20ns)
.
 
rlUInt16_t reserved2
 Reserved for future use.
 
rlUInt16_t dummyVal
 Dummy Count value.
Number of dummy bytes added per chirp
For 12-bit ADC data, 12 * Dummy Value
For 14-bit ADC data, 14 * Dummy Value
For 16-bit ADC data, 16 * Dummy Value
Valid range: 0 to 2048.
.
